<br>
    We encountered a group of people from Tolkien's Revenge when entering the Plane of Growth this evening.  We had reserved the zone nearly two weeks ahead of time using the calendar and were surprised to find them fighting in the zone.  When I asked them what they were up to they said &quot;we're just an exp group&quot;  and that they did not count as a raid.  They refused to leave the zone and continued hunting as the night wore on.  Further questioning lead to the response &quot;of petition a GM&quot;.  I did this as was told that Verant will not take a position on on reservations, this is enforced by players.<br>
<br>
    Should you run into members of this guild, please let them know your opinion of their actions.  The reservation system works nicely to as a system to share the older planes.  It's a shame to see that some folks are selfishly working to destroy the system.<br>
<br>
Rhus <br>
Utopian Guard <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rannin@mtboards>Rannin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Qeynos Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#628CBC>(11/8/02 3:23:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=374.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tolkien's Revenge (</span><hr size=1> Yup, that IS a bummer.  I don't know any TR members personally, but that is pretty self centered and rude behavior from ANYone!  I've been EQing for about a year and half, and for as long as I can remember, the old world Planes and dragons have been reserved on these forums and the players have stuck to them quite well out of respect for eachother.  The fact that someone has gone against it and blatantly ignored an age old tradition greatly bothers me.  It's that kind of behavior that deteriorates the game and ruins everyone's gaming experience.  It's too bad that Verant won't get involved, but I can respect their standpoint.  It IS a player matter.  Players started it.  Players uphold it.  It's just a crying shame that there are some players out there out to ruin it.  But what can we do about it?  Nothing, really.  And that just sucks.<br>
However, we CAN take heart in the fact that perhaps one day we'll run into some of these people in-game, and those people will need our help with something, and we can tell them to take a long walk off a short pier!  Hahahahahaha!!<br>
<br>
Walk safe, and may the Four Winds bring you much fun and profit!<br>
<br>
-Rannin Seawolfe, master archer and thie. . . er, &quot;Treasure Hunter&quot;! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=neext>NEExt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>QHills and Clueless</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#628CBC>(11/8/02 5:00:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=374.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tolkien's Revenge (</span><hr size=1> Whats the big deal?  I don't get it.  There are enough mobs in there to keep the average mid-lvl guild busy an entire day.  One extra exp group in zone isn't going to make a difference.<br>
<br>
If you were nice to them instead of harrassing them, maybe they would have called out armor drops they couldn't use.<br>
<br>
-Mok <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=drackorespyritfyst>DrackoreSpyritfyst</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Riding the Planes</span><br>  Posts: 715<br> <font color=#628CBC>(11/8/02 8:17:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=374.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tolkien's Revenge (</span><hr size=1> With the release of PoP, and with the attitudes of this guild, Hanuri (a rose by any other name, lying in a pile of dog crap, still smells like sh!t, remember that), and Phantom Knights (could never be rose if someone came by and pissed rose petals on them)....I say kill the calander.<br>
<br>
We got rid of rotations...how many rants you getting about Trak or that other one (fergot his name..sleeeeepy).  <br>
<br>
Let em die.  Burn baby burn. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fimble>Fimble</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator<BR>Master Cobbler</span><br>  Posts: 508<br> <font color=#628CBC>(11/8/02 8:23:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=374.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tolkien's Revenge (</span><hr size=1> Well... I'm the guild leader of TR, so you're welcome to send me an email at <!--EZCODE MAIL START--><a href="mailto:fimble@sevendragons.net"> fimble@sevendragons.net</a><!--EZCODE MAIL END-->.<br>
<br>
There was no scheduled guild raid last night, and the folks in PoG were there without my knowledge, though I have to admit that if they were just there as an xp group, what harm could they possibly be doing? Were they trying to gank Tunare or training your raid party? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fimble>Fimble</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator<BR>Master Cobbler</span><br>  Posts: 509<br> <font color=#628CBC>(11/8/02 8:28:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=374.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tolkien's Revenge (</span><hr size=1> I'd be opposed to eliminating the calendar. It's a great way of making sure accidents don't happen and 2 guilds plan raids on PoF for the same day. One of those guilds has to tell its members that they wasted their time getting set up.<br>
<br>
Some folks actualy have to set aside RL time, sometimes days in advance, to attend a raid. The calendar is there to reduce the odds that they wasted their time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wikkiwikwikwikwikwikki>wikkiwikwik wikwikwikki</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Riding the Planes</span><br>  Posts: 619<br> <font color=#628CBC>(11/8/02 8:35:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=374.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   ...</span><hr size=1> Keep the calendar. Works alot more then it doesnt. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=quisss>Quisss</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Giant Squishies in Rathe</span><br>  Posts: 237<br> <font color=#628CBC>(11/8/02 10:01:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=374.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tolkien's Revenge (</span><hr size=1> I have no problems with anyone in TR but this was not a nice thing that those who were exping did.<br>
<br>
I was with Rhus in POG last night when this occured. IMHO one exp group does not make a huge difference but, when a plane is reserved players should respect the reservation and:<br>
<br>
a. not enter the plane knowing its reserved<br>
or<br>
b. leave once the party that reserved the plane arrives<br>
<br>
We had high hopes of killing a lot of the East side mobs but upon entry to the zone almost all of them had been removed. Thus lowering the reserved parties chances at drops, gems, plat and spells. <br>
<br>
Its all about respect of your fellow players and treating them as you would want to be treated. If this is whats to be expected from TR then the next time they reserve a plane I suppose I will have an EXP group there too. What comes around goes around. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fimble>Fimble</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator<BR>Master Cobbler</span><br>  Posts: 512<br> <font color=#628CBC>(11/8/02 11:11:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=374.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tolkien's Revenge (</span><hr size=1> Yeah, I agree, Quiss and will be talking to some members. The folks who were in there were all very new members (less than 24 hours). But I'd like to hear from them why this happened before heads start rolling.<br>
<br>
Since I oversee and run the calendar, you can bet yer sweet bippy that TR follows the rules to the letter. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=crystilla>crystilla</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Egging EW</span><br>  Posts: 386<br> <font color=#628CBC>(11/8/02 11:22:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=374.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tolkien's Revenge (</span><hr size=1> This issue will always happen, but I feel it would be worse without any reservation system.<br>
<br>
One group (to them) may not hurt a raid for another guild, but they don't know the intentions of that raid or the targets of that raid - ie is it a cash pharming raid, armor, experience working as a team, etc.<br>
<br>
The reservation system, IMO, benefits those it should - those guilds who still need something from the zone (armor, raid experience, etc.).  <br>
<br>
How many places have an abundance of mobs where a guild can go and kill mobs for hours (with no one else around to bother) to help train its youth on proper raid techniques?  I doubt people would leave BW, DL, ME or another zone so a raid could occur.  In a plane, you get several hours of together time, working together, dying together perhaps.<br>
<br>
Just one thought I had that I've never seen listed before on these posts (at least the ones I've read).<br>
<br>
:-)<br>
Crys <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lupuri>Lupuri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lonely in Kera Ridge</span><br>  Posts: 167<br> <font color=#628CBC>(11/8/02 11:24:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=374.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tolkien's Revenge (</span><hr size=1> honestly, a group of 6 in pog while you raiding there for armor is no big deal.<br>
there is more then enough mobs in there for a raid of a mid level guild to kill all night and have just as much fun.<br>
<br>
if i was in there and a raid walked in and told me to get out, i would without a doubt laugh my ass off! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vowwmt>VowwMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blackburrow Trainee</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#628CBC>(11/8/02 1:40:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=374.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tolkien's Revenge (</span><hr size=1> I think PoG is sort of a special case based on how huge it is.  The single group there should offer to let the guild raiding there for armor drops, have the drops...if that polite offer is refused, you know there are about 30 other zones a group can go to to grind some xp without ganking someone's raid. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=neext>NEExt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>QHills and Clueless</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#628CBC>(11/8/02 4:48:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=374.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tolkien's Revenge (</span><hr size=1> Its not like they zoned in and took half your plane of Hate or Fear.  Fimble, don't let this guy provoke you.  <br>
<br>
If you people expect everyone that exp groups in growth from time to time to check a calendar before they do it.  We are probably gonna see a &quot;rant&quot; every time you reserve it.  Wake up... =/<br>
<br>
-Mok <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sonaldor>Sonaldor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Qeynos Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#628CBC>(11/8/02 6:18:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=374.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tolkien's Revenge (</span><hr size=1> The real problem with this is the re-pop time.  The minute it becomes acceptable to ignore the calendar and XP in PoG, or any other old world plane, is the minute these zones become worthless to the rest of us that still need zones like these.<br>
<br>
There was only one group up there when we came in, no idea how long they had been there, but they had been there long enough to kill enough mobs that we got to kill 3 at our first camp spot, and track was completely clean and we had to move. <br>
<br>
That's a pretty substantial amount of mobs IMHO, and that was only one group.  Mobs that don't come back for 24 hours or longer.  Now just imagine if this was a FFA XP zone, with several groups hunting there at any given time.  <br>
<br>
Yep, that's right, not a damn thing left for anyone that actually needs the place.  <br>
<br>
That is the reason that the calendar cannot be ignored, because when people start thinking that it is OK to break it and just screw the rest of us cause they are uber, that is what will happen.<br>
<br>
Sonaldor<br>
Utopian Guard<br>
