I NEED the 6k I can pull out of there per hour in cash drops just as much as someone in your guild needs the noctavigant bracer that may drop.  Truth being that most guilds would do as well or better to farm Kael arena vs. the drop rates in PoG -- unless you are after named in PoG, in which case you'd do well to let single groups clear away some of the trash there.   I really think the friendly thing is to a) respect a scheduled raid but also recognize that b) a guild looking for armor drops may be able to propose a decent solution to the problem that a single xp group there may present to their plans.<br>
<br>
